New parser helper in Source/UniPlanOptionParsing.cpp
(companion to TryConsumeStringOrFileOption):

    bool TryConsumeStringOrFileOrAppendFileOption(
        const std::string &InToken,
        const std::vector<std::string> &InArgs,
        size_t &InOutIndex,
        const std::string &InFlagName,      // "--investigation"
        const std::string &InFileFlagName,  // "--investigation-file"
        const std::string &InAppendFlagName,// "--investigation-append-file"
        const std::string &InFieldName,     // "investigation" (key into mAppendFields)
        std::string &OutValue,
        bool &OutValueSet,
        std::set<std::string> &OutAppendFields,
        std::string &OutError);

Semantics:

- If InToken matches InFlagName: consume <text> arg, set OutValue,
  OutValueSet=true, do NOT add to OutAppendFields. Return true.
- If InToken matches InFileFlagName: consume <path> arg,
  TryReadFileToString into OutValue, OutValueSet=true, do NOT add
  to OutAppendFields. Return true.
- If InToken matches InAppendFlagName: consume <path> arg,
  TryReadFileToString into OutValue, OutValueSet=true, add
  InFieldName to OutAppendFields. Return true.
- Multiple matches in one parser invocation (e.g., caller sets
  both --investigation and --investigation-append-file) are
  detected by the caller: if OutValueSet was true before the
  current match, return false with OutError = "mutually exclusive
  flags for <FieldName>".

New shared handler helper in Source/UniPlanHelpers.h (or adjacent):

    // Compute the effective new value for a field given the current
    // bundle value, the option-supplied value, and whether append
    // semantics were requested.
    std::string ComputeAppendOrReplace(
        const std::string &InExistingValue,
        const std::string &InNewValue,
        bool InAppend);

    inline std::string ComputeAppendOrReplace(
        const std::string &InExistingValue,
        const std::string &InNewValue,
        bool InAppend)
    {
        if (!InAppend)
            return InNewValue;
        if (InExistingValue.empty())
            return InNewValue;
        return InExistingValue + "\n\n" + InNewValue;
    }

